  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A complaint from the speaker to the police",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Police Headquarters says that Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena has submitted a written complaint to the Inspector General of Police regarding the threats made to the Members of Parliament through social media in connection with the polling for the appointment of a successor President.",
        "The letter presented by the speaker was forwarded by the Inspector General of Police to the Deputy Inspector General of Criminal Investigation Department and then forwarded to the Computer Crime Division of the Criminal Investigation Department.",
        "The Police Headquarters also says that the Criminal Investigation Department has reported the facts to the court through a B report regarding this incident.",
        "The Computer Crime Investigation Unit of the Criminal Investigation Department has started investigations to arrest people who are making, creating and distributing certain statements on social media networks threatening parliamentarians."
      ],
